*Case decline*

This measures the decline of cases in a given reference period e.g. last month in comparison with the same month last year.

This is calculated as follows;

Decline(%) = (a-b)/a

a -  previous is the period offset of 12 months from actual period of reference

b - actual is the period of reference

*Definitions*

*Report completeness (%)* 

Numerator = Actual health facilities reporting/

Denominator = Expected health facilities to report

*Report timeliness (%)* 

Numerator = Actual health facilities reporting on time

Denominator = Actual health facilities reporting

*Completeness by variables (%)* 

Numerator = Count of values reported for key data value that is representative of the data element

Denominator = Expected reports from all health facilities assign the dataSet that reports the variable

*Interpretations*


Consistency between variables here is being measured by computing the difference between two related data elements that would typically be validated with validation rules.


In this case, inconsistencies between data elements are when the difference between these variables is negative or the value of the left-side variable is more than the right-side and this would be flagged red.

*DEFINITIONS:*
Closing balance = Opening balance + Received - Distributed - Redistributed - Discarded -->Automatically calculated indicator to count the remaining items at the end of the period
Stock on hand = physical stock count at the end of the period
Usable stock = Opening balance + received
Coverage time = Usable stock / Distributed + Discarded + Redistributed = nb. of months

Stock discrepancy = Stock on hand - closing balance
If discrepancy = 0 and 9 --> Stock on hand = closing balance (green cell) - acceptable discrepancy -
If discrepancy < 0 --> closing balance > stock on hand (dark red cell)
If discrepancy > 9 --> closing balance < stock on hand (light red cell)

dataElements.description: Number of cases classified as indigenous with recurrence of asexual parasitaemia of the same genotype(s) that caused the original illness, due to incomplete clearance of asexual parasites after antimalarial treatment.
